node.text:
We're kicking off our first est film production with a momentous Malvern Home renovation by @dohertydesignstudio from est magazine issue #35.
.
Tapping into its rich architectural past and 1980s new wave bones, @dohertydesignstudio have skilfully commandeered an epic journey to reinvent this Melbourne family home. An original 1980's design by architect Peter McIntyre. .
.
Experience the entire home via the link in profile or read the full feature in est magazine issue #35. .
.
Design @dohertydesignstudio
Building design @arialexander
Builder @north_building_group 
Styling @heathernetteking 
Florals and assitant styling @rachelpolivkastylist 
Art consultant @gb.art.consulting 
Landscape design @benscott_design 
Videography @richardlipp.studio
Words @meganmayrawson
Art @tompolo @liamsnootle @anyapesce @oocaleb @davidjamesgriggs @christianthompsonartist #leekyoung-hwa 
Furniture & Objects @domoaustralia @lightlydesign @loomtowels @fenton_and_fenton @abode_living @moderntimesau @ajarfurniture @lamarzoccohomeau

node.text:
Great land. Great architecture. Great living. In an est exclusive, we feature three unique films by Rob Mills Architecture & Interiors (RMA). Australian-based RMA’s latest project, a ground-breaking residence in Byron Bay incorporates Mill’s signature use of drama, curves, lines, light and a reflection of the qualities of the land.
.
View all three films via link in profile.
.
Videography @collider__
Creative Direction | Design @robmillsarchitects

node.title: Exclusive | The latest architectural project by Rob Mills

node.text:
HOME OF THE MONTH | St Huberts by Robson Rak
​.
St Huberts by @robsonrakarchitects was our most-viewed home feature on estliving.com in August. 
​.
@robsonrakarchitects’s commitment to refining the building’s period features is matched by the respectful and highly intentional curation of novel design.
​.
​By intentionally balancing the aesthetic scales with austerity and design clarity, @robsonrakarchitects demonstrate how period architecture can successfully support 21st-century living.
​.
​Visit estliving.com for a full home tour of St Huberts – link in profile. 
​.
​​Design @robsonrakarchitects
​Photography @markroperphotography
​Build @ddbdesigndevelopment
​Landscape design @cos.design
​Words @creative_concierge
​.
​https://www.estliving.com/st-huberts-robson-rak/

node.text:
ARCHITECTURE | Fan Forest Houses
​.
​Located at the foot of a forest in Nova Ponente, Northern Italy, the Fan Forest Houses by @bergmeisterwolf are constructed on concrete platforms and staggered to 'fan' across the landscape. 
​.
​The collection of gabled cabins are designed to blend into the dark forest beyond, while the light-laden interiors take in the rolling countryside.
​.
​Design @bergmeisterwolf
​Photography @sangu
​.
​https://www.estliving.com/

INTERIORS | Pacific Palisades 
​.
Located in the Los Angeles neighbourhood of the same name, the ​Pacific Palisades Residence creates a sense of sanctuary for those that live there through arched motifs, expansive ceiling heights and considered openings that welcome natural light. 
​.
A collaboration between architecture firm @mikeholzarchitect and interior designers @studiolifestyle_, the serenity cultivated in each space is captured in the outdoor living area too – manifesting barefoot luxury from inside, out. 
​​.
​Architecture @mikeholzarchitect
​Design @studiolifestyle_
​Styling @stellaflynn
​Photography @samfroststudio
​.

node.text:
INTERIORS | VDC Residence
​.
​"Authenticity is to create a space where you feel at home. A place easy to access aiming to identify with the rich historical environment rather than escape it, reintegrating social and cultural value into the space." 
​– Vincent Van Duysen
​.
Vincent Van Duysen's words on authenticity from his interview with est couldn't ring more true in the renovation of the VCD Residence, completed in 2010. This enduring project saw the existing home reclaim its stately heritage and a pool house extension create a sincere connection to the surrounding gardens. 
.
Design @vincentvanduysen
​Photography @binet.helene, @francoishalard & @koenvandamme 
​.
​https://www.estliving.com/

​​.
​Design @morqarchitecture 
​Photography @giulioaristide
​.

node.text:
DESIGNER INSIDER | Supersalone Milan 2021
​.
​This week est will be on the ground in Milan for Salone del Mobile with Australian designer @nikolaikotlarczyk, who will be sharing his highlights from the week via our Instagram stories.
​.
​We kick off on Monday with the event 'I'll be your Mirror' with interiors designed by @elisaossinostudio, which encourages the viewer to 'contemplate their own significance and appearance within space and time'. 
​.
​In 2019, Elissa Ossino presented Perfect Darkness as part of Milan Design Week (pictured); an apartment installation where past met future, darkness met light and silence met sound.
.
Follow along with our hashtag #estmilanmoments to see Nikolai's insider scoop over the coming week – and ​DM us if you would like to see us swing by your event this year.
​.
​Interior Design @elissaossinostudio 
​Project @h.plus.o 
​Photography @giorgiopossentiphotography 
​Project H + O Apartment Gallery
​.
​https://www.estliving.com/

node.text:
HOME TOUR | Les Voisine
​.
​Made up of three distinct yet interconnected houses, Les Voisines by  @appareilarchitecture blurs the line between shared and private spaces.
​.
​Meaning ‘The Neighbours’ in French, Les Voisines adopts an unconventional co-living layout. Secluded in the unfrequented forests of Quebec, the home offers a retreat for both inhabiting parties – a space where they can come together while remaining sufficiently apart.
​.
​Read more about Les Voisine on estliving.com – link in profile. 
​.
​Architecture @appareilarchitecture 
​Interior Design @lysannepepin
​Photography @michaudfelix_photo
​Words @hollybeadle 
​.
​https://www.estliving.com/les-voisines-appareil-architecture/
